      "writtenOn": "2026-03-24T09:53:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is already automated.\n\nThe check is implemented as a Bazel test (similar to the license checks in Gerrit core). When it fails, it provides exact instructions on how to refresh the allowlist.\n\nFor example, if I remove `jgroups` from the allowlist and run:\n\n```\n$ bazel test plugins/high-availability:check_high-availability_third_party_runtime_jars\n[...]\n\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d Test output for //plugins/high-availability:check_high-availability_third_party_runtime_jars:\n--- /var/folders/cx/dy8y9cb54cq0nch6gb2k31nw0000gq/T/tmp.1qmO1VCk/allowlist.norm\t2026-03-24 09:36:35\n+++ /var/folders/cx/dy8y9cb54cq0nch6gb2k31nw0000gq/T/tmp.1qmO1VCk/generated.norm\t2026-03-24 09:36:35\n@@ -1,2 +1,3 @@\n failsafe\n+jgroups\n jgroups-kubernetes\n\nFAIL: Packaged third-party JAR set changed.\n\nIf expected, refresh the allowlist with:\n  bazelisk build plugins/high-availability:check_high-availability_third_party_runtime_jars_manifest\n  cp bazel-bin/check_high-availability_third_party_runtime_jars_manifest.txt plugins/high-availability/high-availability_third_party_runtime_jars.allowlist.txt\n```\n\nthe test fails with a diff and prints the commands needed to update the allowlist.\n\nSo the workflow is:\n\n* run the test\n* review the diff\n* follow the printed instructions if the change is expected\n\nHappy to improve this further if you have suggestions.",
